682
00:51:39,196 --> 00:51:42,461
<i>I'm not disputing</i>
<i>that fact, Mr. Davies.</i>
<i>It may be a fine letter.</i>

683
00:51:42,533 --> 00:51:45,627
But if it's an honest letter,
it's none of my business to read it.

684
00:51:45,703 --> 00:51:48,263
And if it isn't,
I don't want to.

685
00:51:48,339 --> 00:51:52,105
- Is that my letter you're showin'?
- Yes.

686
00:51:54,044 --> 00:51:57,138
What right have you got
to show my letter?

687
00:51:57,214 --> 00:51:59,682
- Don't raise your voice, rustler!
- He's right, Smith.

688
00:51:59,750 --> 00:52:03,015
-I told him I'd keep it for him.
-I asked you to make sure
that it was delivered.

689
00:52:03,087 --> 00:52:05,521
I'm sorry. I was just trying
to prove that you were--

690
00:52:05,589 --> 00:52:07,750
It's enough to be hanged
by bullying outlaws...

691
00:52:07,825 --> 00:52:10,453
without having your private thoughts
handed round to them for a joke.

692
00:52:10,527 --> 00:52:12,757
I said I'm sorry.
I was merely trying--

693
00:52:12,830 --> 00:52:14,821
I don't care
what you were doing!

694
00:52:14,898 --> 00:52:17,093
I didn't write that letter
to be passed around!

695
00:52:17,167 --> 00:52:20,295
- It's none of these
murderers' business!
- I made no promise, son.

696
00:52:20,371 --> 00:52:24,137
I thought there was
one white man among you.
But I was wrong.

697
00:52:24,208 --> 00:52:26,768
- Give me my letter.
- <i>I'll see that she gets it.</i>

698
00:52:26,844 --> 00:52:29,574
Oh, I wouldn't have her
touch it now.

699
00:52:29,646 --> 00:52:33,173
In that case,
give him back the letter.

700
00:52:35,919 --> 00:52:38,149
Your wife ought
to hear from you, son.

701
00:52:38,222 --> 00:52:41,316
None of us could be as kind
and understanding as this letter.

702
00:52:41,392 --> 00:52:44,828
She'll want to keep it...
for your children.

703
00:52:47,331 --> 00:52:49,765
- I'm sorry.
- <i>[ Ma Shouting ]</i>
<i>Hey, the Mex!.</i>

704
00:52:49,833 --> 00:52:53,701
- <i>[ Gunshots ]</i>
- Spread out! He might have a gun!

705
00:52:53,771 --> 00:52:56,205
Mapes. Winder.
Keep an eye on those two.

706
00:52:56,273 --> 00:52:59,606
<i>[ Gunfire Continues ]</i>

707
00:53:07,518 --> 00:53:09,679
<i>[ Gunshots Continue ]</i>

708
00:53:11,522 --> 00:53:14,685
<i>[ Sound of Gunfire</i>
<i>Fades Into Distance ]</i>

709
00:53:17,828 --> 00:53:19,762
<i>[ Gunfire Stops ]</i>

710
00:53:44,154 --> 00:53:46,145
- Where's he hit?
- In the leg.

711
00:53:49,092 --> 00:53:51,890
Here's his gun.

712
00:53:51,962 --> 00:53:54,328
Well,
I guess we know now, don't we?

713
00:53:54,398 --> 00:53:56,491
Look.

714
00:53:58,268 --> 00:54:01,101
- Say, that's Larry Kinkaid's gun.
- <i>Where did you get this?</i>

715
00:54:02,673 --> 00:54:04,937
Somebody will take this bullet
out of my leg, I'll tell you.

716
00:54:05,008 --> 00:54:07,238
Ha!
So he speaks American!

717
00:54:07,311 --> 00:54:10,246
And ten other languages,
my dear.

718
00:54:10,314 --> 00:54:12,960
But I don't tell anything
I don't want to in any of them.

719
00:54:13,094 --> 00:54:15,619
My leg, please.

720
00:54:15,696 --> 00:54:19,359
I wish to stand upright
when you come to your pleasure.

721
00:54:19,433 --> 00:54:22,869
- Somebody lend me a knife.
I'll take it out myself.
- Don't give him no knife.

722
00:54:22,937 --> 00:54:25,963
He can throw a knife better
than most men can shoot.

723
00:54:26,040 --> 00:54:28,406
Better than any of you,
no doubt.

724
00:54:28,476 --> 00:54:30,501
But if you're afraid, I promise
to give the knife back...

725
00:54:30,578 --> 00:54:32,512
handle first.

726
00:54:32,580 --> 00:54:35,140
I'll do it.

727
00:54:48,963 --> 00:54:51,022
<i>[ Fabric Ripping ]</i>

728
00:55:08,048 --> 00:55:11,279
He's very polite, but has
no stomach for blood, eh?

729
