735
00:55:57,064 --> 00:55:59,259
- Now where'd you get that gun?
- Found it.

736
00:55:59,333 --> 00:56:01,392
- Where?
- Lying in the road.

737
00:56:01,468 --> 00:56:04,164
- You're a liar.
- I thought we might find
somebody to send it back by.

738
00:56:04,238 --> 00:56:06,968
You're a liar!

739
00:56:07,041 --> 00:56:09,134
And you're a blind fool.

740
00:56:09,210 --> 00:56:11,576
I asked you
where you got it.

741
00:56:11,645 --> 00:56:13,579
<i>No sabe.</i>

742
00:56:13,647 --> 00:56:17,777
- Well, that's the truth.
He <i>did</i> find it.
- Undoubtedly.

743
00:56:17,852 --> 00:56:19,843
Won't you even read it?

744
00:56:22,223 --> 00:56:24,453
Is it because you've
made up your minds?

745
00:56:24,525 --> 00:56:26,857
Or you believe
everybody else has...

746
00:56:26,927 --> 00:56:29,691
and you're afraid to stand up
for what you feel is right?

747
00:56:29,763 --> 00:56:31,890
You heard what Martin said
about showing his letter.

748
00:56:31,966 --> 00:56:34,901
What does it matter
to the man or his wife
who sees this letter...

749
00:56:34,969 --> 00:56:37,597
if it saves him
from hanging?

750
00:56:37,671 --> 00:56:40,799
It's a beautiful letter.
Read it, and you'll know...

751
00:56:40,875 --> 00:56:44,641
- he's not the kind of man
who could steal or kill.
- Maybe.

752
00:56:44,712 --> 00:56:47,510
But all that kind
of argument in the world
can't stand up against...

753
00:56:47,581 --> 00:56:50,482
branded cattle, no bill of sale
and a dead man's gun.

754
00:56:50,584 --> 00:56:53,815
Gentlemen, I suggest
we act as a unit...

755
00:56:53,888 --> 00:56:56,948
so there will be no question
of mistaken reprisals.

756
00:56:57,024 --> 00:56:59,015
Mr. Davies...

757
00:56:59,093 --> 00:57:02,256
are you willing
to abide by majority decision?

758
00:57:05,366 --> 00:57:09,359
- How about the rest of you?
- Sure. Majority rules with me.

759
00:57:09,436 --> 00:57:12,837
Everybody with Mr. Davies
in putting this off and
turning it over to the courts...

760
00:57:12,907 --> 00:57:14,841
step over there.

761
00:58:17,371 --> 00:58:19,703
Excuse me.

762
00:59:21,702 --> 00:59:24,398
Seven.

763
00:59:24,471 --> 00:59:28,305
Not a majority, I believe,
Mr. Davies.

764
00:59:38,752 --> 00:59:41,277
<i>[ Tetley ]</i>
<i>Any other message</i>
<i>you'd like to leave, Martin?</i>

765
00:59:48,095 --> 00:59:51,087
[ Sobbing ]
I-- I don't wanna die.

766
00:59:51,165 --> 00:59:53,258
- I'd like to make a confession.
- I didn't do it.

767
00:59:53,333 --> 00:59:56,325
- And about time.
- To a priest.

768
00:59:56,403 --> 00:59:58,803
<i>There's no priest here.</i>

769
00:59:58,872 --> 01:00:01,602
This man can hear me
and take it to a priest.

770
01:00:01,675 --> 01:00:04,838
- <i>[ Old Man Whimpering ]</i>
- <i>All right. Get along with it.</i>

771
01:00:04,912 --> 01:00:07,642
I don't want to die.

772
01:00:13,987 --> 01:00:18,447
- I don't want to die.
- Bring him along.

773
01:00:20,627 --> 01:00:24,791
