Protesting ]

774
01:00:24,865 --> 01:00:29,268
I didn't do anything.
I didn't--

775
01:00:32,806 --> 01:00:36,207
That must have been
an awfully busy life.

776
01:00:36,276 --> 01:00:40,212
[ Pancho, Mexican
Praying, Indistinct ]

777
01:00:47,020 --> 01:00:49,181
[ Chattering ]

778
01:00:50,991 --> 01:00:53,482
Farnley, you,
Gabe Hart and Gerald...

779
01:00:53,560 --> 01:00:56,961
- will whip the horses out.
- No, not me.

780
01:00:57,030 --> 01:01:00,431
Any volunteers?

781
01:01:06,573 --> 01:01:09,872
I'll do it
if no one else will.

782
01:01:09,943 --> 01:01:13,572
- I won't do it.
- You'll do it.

783
01:01:13,647 --> 01:01:17,242
- I-- I can't.
- We'll see to it that you can.

784
01:01:17,317 --> 01:01:21,583
The kid's seen enough already.
Why don't you let him alone?

785
01:01:21,655 --> 01:01:25,591
This is not your affair, Carter.
Thank you just the same.

786
01:01:27,161 --> 01:01:30,494
I'll have no female boys
bearin' my name.

787
01:01:30,564 --> 01:01:32,930
You'll do your part...

788
01:01:33,000 --> 01:01:35,264
and say nothing more.

789
01:01:39,940 --> 01:01:42,738
- What did he say?
- I ain't no priest.

790
01:01:42,809 --> 01:01:46,006
For God's sake, man.
At least say whether
we'd better wait.

791
01:01:46,079 --> 01:01:49,810
Well, I ain't no priest.
I don't know.

792
01:01:51,084 --> 01:01:53,279
[ Sobbing ]

793
01:01:53,353 --> 01:01:55,844
No, thanks.

794
01:01:55,923 --> 01:01:58,653
[ Sobbing Continues ]

795
01:02:08,068 --> 01:02:11,003
I'll give you
two minutes to pray.

796
01:02:29,389 --> 01:02:32,586
[ Praying In Spanish ]

797
01:02:52,412 --> 01:02:56,075
<i>[ Prayer Continues ]</i>

798
01:03:02,789 --> 01:03:04,916
<i>[ Prayer Continues ]</i>

799
01:03:04,992 --> 01:03:06,983
Time's up.

800
01:03:07,060 --> 01:03:10,621
Will you find someone
to look out for my wife
and children?

801
01:03:10,697 --> 01:03:12,961
Take some older woman along.
It's not going to be easy.

802
01:03:13,033 --> 01:03:16,833
- Your family will be all right.
- My parents are dead,
but Miriam's live in Ohio.

803
01:03:16,903 --> 01:03:19,531
Kinkaid didn't want to sell
those cattle, so maybe his wife
will buy them back...

804
01:03:19,606 --> 01:03:21,904
- <i>for enough to cover their travel.</i>
- Tie 'em up!

805
01:03:21,975 --> 01:03:24,603
[ Martin ]
I suppose it's no good telling
you again we're innocent.

806
01:03:24,678 --> 01:03:27,511
- No good.
- It's not for myself I'm asking--

807
01:03:27,581 --> 01:03:30,106
Other men with families
have had to die for this.

808
01:03:30,183 --> 01:03:32,174
It's too bad,
but it's justice.

809
01:03:32,252 --> 01:03:34,186
What do you care
about justice?

810
01:03:34,254 --> 01:03:36,188
You don't care
if you've got the right men!

811
01:03:36,256 --> 01:03:38,520
All you know is somebody's
got to be punished!

812
01:03:38,592 --> 01:03:42,722
There's nobody to look out
for them in a strange place.
Can't you understand that?

813
01:03:42,796 --> 01:03:45,629
This is a fine company
for a man to die with.

814
01:03:45,699 --> 01:03:48,190
- Shut up! You shut up!
- <i>You</i> shut up!

815
01:03:51,305 --> 01:03:54,206
[ Overlapping Shouts ]

816
01:03:58,412 --> 01:04:02,178
Get 'em off me!
Pull that guy off.

817
01:04:05,385 --> 01:04:07,615
Come on. Tear 'em loose.
Don't let 'em do that.

818
01:04:08,955 --> 01:04:12,584
- Stop it! Stop it, you fools!
- Aw, you stop it!

819
01:04:12,659 --> 01:04:14,820
<i>[ Tetley ]</i>
<i>Keep him there!.</i>

820
01:04:16,997 --> 01:04:19,090
All right.
Put them up.

821
